\subsection{Results}
\subsubsection{Significantly expressed miRNAs}
Significantly differentially expressed miRNAs. Fold change is retinoblastoma/normal.


<<dePval,results=tex,echo=F>>=
resSig<-subset(res,res$PValue < myPval)
displayColumnSetup<-c('s','f','f','e','e')
#names(resSig)<-c('miRNA','baseMean','bNorm','bRB','fc','log2fc','pval','padj')
myXtableOne<-xtable(resSig[order(resSig$PValue)[1:30],],type=tex,caption=paste("Significant (P<",myPval,") differential expression before the correction for multiple testing (top 30)"),digits=3,display=displayColumnSetup)

print(myXtableOne,include.rownames=TRUE, size="\\footnotesize")
@

After correcting for multiple testing (Benjamini-Hochberg procedure),
\Sexpr{nrow(subset(res,FDR<.05))} miRNAs were differentially
expressed.
