\subsubsection{Upregulated miRNAs}
Identifying upregulated miRNAs by fold change is problematic, as the
metric does not scale well for analyses with large variations in
expression and will be dominated by low and zero count miRNAs.

One approach is to take the subset of miRNAs with logConc greater
than the median.

<<upreg,results=tex,echo=F>>=
regs<-subset(res,logConc>median(res$logConc))
#names(regs)<-c('miRNA','baseMean','bNorm','bRB','fc','log2fc','pval','padj')

upRegs<-regs[ order(-regs$logFC)[1:20], ]
myXtableTwo<-xtable(upRegs,type=tex,caption=paste("Strongly upregulated miRNAs in ",gsub('_','-',samp1),sep=""),digits=3,display=displayColumnSetup)
print(myXtableTwo,include.rownames=TRUE, size="\\footnotesize")
@

